<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-366-768  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 366 768.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  April 1990 v111 n4 p78(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Image is the next information frontier. (information storage andretrieval)</TITLE><AUTHOR>MacWhorter, David E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Integrated imaging systems can store digitized documents onoptical disk for use by an unlimited number of authorized users.andO;There are three main issues that must be addressed when a companydecides to improve its information flow: storage, accessibilityand file integrity needs and limitations.andP;  Storage of paper filesis usually finite and determined by office size.andP;  If more than oneindividual needs a file at any one time, alternative methods mustbe used.andP;  Lack of file integrity results in higher costs forretrieving documents, if they can be retrieved at all.andP;  Anintegrated imaging system would allow businesses and governmentoffices to better manage all of their information.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalOffice ProceduresOffice AutomationDocument Management SystemsImage processingRecords ManagementInformation SystemsFile Management.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>